<span id="vi.XIII-p2"></span>————————————

<span id="vi.XIII-p3"></span>Of the goodness of God explained in the
creation of things, and of the Trinity as found in the first words of
Genesis. The story concerning the origin of the world (Gen. I.) is
allegorically explained, and he applies it to those things which God
works for sanctified and blessed man. Finally, he makes an end of this
work, having implored eternal rest from God.

